transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra. Quinn speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I was wanting to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: Okie dokie. Let me go ahead and pull up your account here one second.

Speaker 2: Sorry, your name is Clyde?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Alrighty, sir. I do see you are a VIP here. Do you mind if I ask why you're canceling?

Speaker 1: Well, it's just not working.

Speaker 2: Oh, it's not working. Okay, well, this is generally, you know, this is a body chemistry type of medication.

Speaker 1: You know, generally it is just a little switch maybe to a new manufacturer of Viagra can usually help out a lot.

Speaker 2: I can send you some more pills for free and obviously stop these ones and see if those are working for you better.

Speaker 1: No, let's just stop the prescription. I've got three or four bottles of Viagra.

Speaker 2: Well, yeah, three or four bottles of something different that's not working for you is not really going to, you know, I'm going to send you something different.

Speaker 1: No, I'm just saying I've tried it on and off and it's not worked and I'm going to go in a different direction.

Speaker 2: Well, you haven't tried what I'm going to send you yet, though, sir. You haven't tried this yet.

Speaker 1: And what are you sending me?

Speaker 2: I'm sending you something different. I don't want to send you the same thing that's not working for you.

Speaker 1: I'm going to send you one of our newest Viagras from France. This is our newest Pfizer Viagra.

Speaker 2: If you don't want it, fine. I'm just trying to give you the...

Speaker 1: Yeah, for the new year. That was our newest one last year.

Speaker 2: I don't think so. Just cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: All right, you're canceled. You have a good day.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.
